Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - This paper primarily focuses on the evolution dynamics of internet topology, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper discusses the generative model used to replicate the evolution dynamics observed on the internet historic data, which can be considered as a social and information network. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper analyzes the network evolution mechanisms that control the obtained topology properties, which can be related to systems and control. 
4. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) - The paper uses computational methods to simulate and analyze the evolution dynamics of internet topology, which can be considered as computational engineering. 
5. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper provides insights on correlations between various structural characteristics of complex networks, which can be related to information theory.
